## 2. Image Generation Providers (third-party SaaS)

MashupForge does not host its own image models. Generated images
are produced by calling the following third-party APIs, each under
their own terms of service:

- **Leonardo.ai** — https://leonardo.ai/terms
- **MiniMax** — https://api.minimaxi.chat/
- **OpenAI GPT Image** — https://openai.com/policies/row-terms-of-use/
- **Google Gemini ("Nano Banana")** — https://ai.google.dev/terms

Users of MashupForge must hold valid API keys (or, for the
MiniMax provider, an appropriate MiniMax account) and are bound by
those providers' respective terms. MashupForge passes user prompts
to the chosen provider verbatim; the providers themselves are
responsible for content moderation, billing, and IP policy.

