## 4. Persistence

### idb-keyval — Apache License 2.0
Copyright (c) 2016, Jake Archibald.
https://github.com/jakearchibald/idb-keyval
A tiny promise-based key-value store backed by IndexedDB. Used as
the browser-side persistence layer for the post lifecycle state
machine, the user's niches/genres configuration, and the
SettingsModal draft state.

The Tauri desktop build additionally uses `tauri-plugin-store`
(linked below) for OS-level persistence; the choice between
backends is made at runtime by the post-lifecycle state machine.

